<paragraph id="8B85B738FFE2622BFF12F987D0D3F9A4" blockId="3.[151,743,1560,1623]" box="[151,400,1597,1623]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">
(
<figureCitation id="1301ABBDFFE2622BFF1AF987D076F9A4" box="[159,309,1597,1623]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–15" captionStartId="4.[152,270,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[175,1410,191,1759]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[171,1417,179,1768]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–15. Males of Hecalina species 1–5. Dorsal habitus 1. Hecalus ghaurii Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; 2. H. lutescens (Distant); 3. H. shanayai sp. nov.; 4. H. tumidus sp. nov.; 5. Thomsonia assymmetricus sp. nov.; 6–10. Lateral habitus. 6. Hecalus ghaurii Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; 7. H. lutescens (Distant); 8. H. shanayai sp. nov.; 9. H. tumidus sp. nov.; 10. T. assymmetricus sp. nov.; 11–15. Face 11. Hecalus ghaurii Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; 12. H. lutescens (Distant); 13. H. shanayai sp. nov.; 14. H. tumidus sp. nov.; 15. T. assymmetricus sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4283984" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4283984/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Figs. 3, 8, 13</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1301ABBDFFE2622BFEC4F987D0CAF9A4" box="[321,393,1597,1623]" captionStart="FIGURES 34–40" captionStartId="7.[152,270,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[173,1404,643,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-210@7.[169,1418,633,1953]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 34–40. Genitalia male Hecalus shanayai sp. nov. 34. Pygofer; 35. Subgenital plate; 36. Style; 37. Aedeagus dorsal view; 38. Aedeagus, lateral view; 39. Aedeagus, ventral view; 40. Connective." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4283990" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4283990/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">34–40</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B85B738FFE2622BFF12F93FD0A9F8F8" blockId="3.[151,1437,1669,2020]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">
Male (
<figureCitation id="1301ABBDFFE2622BFF5AF93FD004F96C" box="[223,327,1669,1695]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–15" captionStartId="4.[152,270,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[175,1410,191,1759]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[171,1417,179,1768]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–15. Males of Hecalina species 1–5. Dorsal habitus 1. Hecalus ghaurii Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; 2. H. lutescens (Distant); 3. H. shanayai sp. nov.; 4. H. tumidus sp. nov.; 5. Thomsonia assymmetricus sp. nov.; 6–10. Lateral habitus. 6. Hecalus ghaurii Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; 7. H. lutescens (Distant); 8. H. shanayai sp. nov.; 9. H. tumidus sp. nov.; 10. T. assymmetricus sp. nov.; 11–15. Face 11. Hecalus ghaurii Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; 12. H. lutescens (Distant); 13. H. shanayai sp. nov.; 14. H. tumidus sp. nov.; 15. T. assymmetricus sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4283984" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4283984/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Figs. 3, 8</figureCitation>
) Color yellowish green to green. Anterior margin of head with transverse submarginal fuscous line, face (
<figureCitation id="1301ABBDFFE2622BFF53F913D064F930" box="[214,295,1705,1731]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–15" captionStartId="4.[152,270,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[175,1410,191,1759]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[171,1417,179,1768]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–15. Males of Hecalina species 1–5. Dorsal habitus 1. Hecalus ghaurii Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; 2. H. lutescens (Distant); 3. H. shanayai sp. nov.; 4. H. tumidus sp. nov.; 5. Thomsonia assymmetricus sp. nov.; 6–10. Lateral habitus. 6. Hecalus ghaurii Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; 7. H. lutescens (Distant); 8. H. shanayai sp. nov.; 9. H. tumidus sp. nov.; 10. T. assymmetricus sp. nov.; 11–15. Face 11. Hecalus ghaurii Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; 12. H. lutescens (Distant); 13. H. shanayai sp. nov.; 14. H. tumidus sp. nov.; 15. T. assymmetricus sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4283984" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4283984/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) brown, gena black, frontoclypeus transverse black striae invisible in middle. Compound eyes black, ocelli yellow. Forewings subhyaline, with diffuse fuscous transverse band across costal margin. Bases of tibial macrosetae and tarsi light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B85B738FFE2622BFF42F8AFD408F868" blockId="3.[151,1437,1669,2020]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Head including eyes as long as width of pronotum. Head produced in front, crown length 0.7x shorter than width between eyes. Face as long as wide; anterior margin of pronotum not extending beyond eyes, more or less parallel with eyes. Frontoclypeus longer than wide; frontal suture, terminating laterad of ocelli. Ocelli near anterior margin, very closely oppressed to eyes. Pronotum length 0.2x as long as wide and 0.9x length of scutellum.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B85B738FFE2622DFF42F81FD1ADF8EF" blockId="3.[151,1437,1669,2020]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,1686,2037]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="578" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis id="B94E6B2AFFE2622BFF42F81FD034F84C" bold="true" box="[199,375,1957,1983]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation id="1301ABBDFFE2622BFE66F81FD370F84C" box="[483,563,1957,1983]" captionStart="FIGURES 34–40" captionStartId="7.[152,270,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[173,1404,643,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-210@7.[169,1418,633,1953]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 34–40. Genitalia male Hecalus shanayai sp. nov. 34. Pygofer; 35. Subgenital plate; 36. Style; 37. Aedeagus dorsal view; 38. Aedeagus, lateral view; 39. Aedeagus, ventral view; 40. Connective." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4283990" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4283990/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) longer than wide, posterior margin triangular, with posterior ½ densely setose. Style (
<figureCitation id="1301ABBDFFE2622BFF65F873D073F817" box="[224,304,1993,2020]" captionStart="FIGURES 34–40" captionStartId="7.[152,270,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[173,1404,643,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-210@7.[169,1418,633,1953]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 34–40. Genitalia male Hecalus shanayai sp. nov. 34. Pygofer; 35. Subgenital plate; 36. Style; 37. Aedeagus dorsal view; 38. Aedeagus, lateral view; 39. Aedeagus, ventral view; 40. Connective." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4283990" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4283990/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
) with preapical lobe obtusely angulate, with few microsetae, apophysis short, 0.25 of the total length. Connective (
<figureCitation id="1301ABBDFFE4622DFEADF92CD038F943" box="[296,379,1686,1712]" captionStart="FIGURES 34–40" captionStartId="7.[152,270,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[173,1404,643,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-210@7.[169,1418,633,1953]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 34–40. Genitalia male Hecalus shanayai sp. nov. 34. Pygofer; 35. Subgenital plate; 36. Style; 37. Aedeagus dorsal view; 38. Aedeagus, lateral view; 39. Aedeagus, ventral view; 40. Connective." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4283990" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4283990/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
) with stem 2x shorter than arms. Aedeagal shaft narrowed apically, broad medially in lateral view, foliate in apical 0.2 with sparsely serrated margin, dorsal margin with short subapical tooth, with pair of slender apical processes half as long as shaft extended anterolaterad, gonopore subapical on ventral margin (
<figureCitation id="1301ABBDFFE4622DFAE1F964D1A2F8EF" captionStart="FIGURES 34–40" captionStartId="7.[152,270,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[173,1404,643,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-210@7.[169,1418,633,1953]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 34–40. Genitalia male Hecalus shanayai sp. nov. 34. Pygofer; 35. Subgenital plate; 36. Style; 37. Aedeagus dorsal view; 38. Aedeagus, lateral view; 39. Aedeagus, ventral view; 40. Connective." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4283990" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4283990/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Figs. 37–39</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
