(Distant)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1301ABBDFFE4622DFBF2F860D451F807" box="[1143,1298,2010,2036]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–15" captionStartId="4.[152,270,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[175,1410,191,1759]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[171,1417,179,1768]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–15. Males of Hecalina species 1–5. Dorsal habitus 1. Hecalus ghaurii Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; 2. H. lutescens (Distant); 3. H. shanayai sp. nov.; 4. H. tumidus sp. nov.; 5. Thomsonia assymmetricus sp. nov.; 6–10. Lateral habitus. 6. Hecalus ghaurii Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; 7. H. lutescens (Distant); 8. H. shanayai sp. nov.; 9. H. tumidus sp. nov.; 10. T. assymmetricus sp. nov.; 11–15. Face 11. Hecalus ghaurii Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan; 12. H. lutescens (Distant); 13. H. shanayai sp. nov.; 14. H. tumidus sp. nov.; 15. T. assymmetricus sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4283984" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4283984/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Figs. 2, 7, 12</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1301ABBDFFE4622DFAA5F860D42BF807" box="[1312,1384,2010,2036]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–33" captionStartId="6.[152,270,1585,1609]" captionTargetBox="[202,1386,355,1550]" captionTargetId="figure-107@6.[192,1395,345,1562]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 27–33. Genitalia male Hecalus lutescens (Distant) 27. Pygofer; 28. Subgenital plate; 29. Style; 30. Aedeagus dorsal view; 31. Aedeagus, lateral view; 32. Aedeagus, ventral view; 33. Connective." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4283988" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4283988/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">27–33</figureCitation>
) but differs in having the aedeagal shaft foliate in the apical 0.2 with a sparsely serrated margin, the dorsal margin with a short subapical tooth, and lacking mid-dorsal lateral expansions which are more distinct in the latter. From 
<taxonomicName id="4C3ACCBBFFE7622EFA04FF01D0B3FF0A" authority="Rao and Ramakrishnan" authorityName="Rao and Ramakrishnan" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hecalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ghauri">
<emphasis id="B94E6B2AFFE7622EFA04FF01D1A1FF0A" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">H. ghauri</emphasis>
Rao and Ramakrishnan
</taxonomicName>
, (
<figureCitation id="1301ABBDFFE7622EFD87FF65D384FF0A" box="[514,711,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–26" captionStartId="5.[152,270,1579,1603]" captionTargetBox="[185,1404,184,1549]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[167,1419,181,1556]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16–26. Genitalia male Hecalus ghaurii Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan 16. Pygofer; 17. Subgenital plate; 18. Style; 19. Aedeagus dorsal view; 20. Aedeagus, lateral view; 21. Aedeagus, ventral view; 22. Connective; 23–26. Label data on Holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4283986" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4283986/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="579">Figs. 19, 20 &amp; 21</figureCitation>
) it can be distinguished by the aedeagal shaft foliate in the apical 0.2 with a sparsely serrated margin, the dorsal margin with a short subapical tooth, and lacking mid-dorsal lateral expansions more distinct in the former.
</paragraph>
